   "body" : "My original problem:\nGiven I start with a brand new wallet,\nAnd I receive 1BTC to Address A,\nAnd I receive 0.08 BTC to Address B,\nAnd I have checked \"Enable coin control features\" in the options:\n\nWhen I go to the send tab,\nAnd I click \"Inputs\" in the coin control section,\nAnd I check only Address B,\n\nThen the \"Amount\" field on the Send page vanishes, and a non-editable Amount displays 0.08.\n\nHow do I send less than the full balance (say, 0.04 BTC) to Address C from Address B?\n![bitcoin-uncensored](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/7917920/9570297/764d01aa-4f55-11e5-996e-74348656cbed.PNG)\n",
